******
[2] Canada (Ontario)
Date: Thu 9 Oct 2014
Source: The Star [edited]
http://www.thestar.com/life/health_wellness/2014/10/08/child_with_muscle_weakness_tests_positive_for_enterovirus_d68_at_sickkids.html


At the Hospital for Sick Children [in Toronto, where] 6 children are currently suffering from muscle weakness linked to respiratory illness, one has tested positive for enterovirus D68 (EV-D68), one has tested positive for rhinovirus, and 2 are still awaiting test results, SickKids associate pediatrician-in-chief Dr Jeremy Friedman said in a news conference Wednesday afternoon [8 Oct 2014]. The other 2 children tested negative for EV-D68. All are under 10.

SickKids Hospital has had 7 confirmed cases of EV-D68 in the last few weeks. The enigmatic respiratory virus has been infecting children across North America since early August [2014], sending thousands of kids to hospital.

The US Centers for Disease Control has alerted doctors to be on the lookout for polio-like symptoms in children diagnosed with enterovirus D68. The disease has recently been linked to polio-like symptoms, such as paralysis.

Friedman would not be drawn on details about the 6 patients at SickKids or the severity of their muscle weakness.

The EV-D68 outbreak appeared to be on a downward trend in Toronto now, he said. "As far as the D68 issue goes, it seems to us in the last week or 2 there are less children being seen with respiratory problems."

Two young patients in [British Columbia] have also suffered paralysis linked to EV-D68, with one on a breathing machine in hospital for more than a month.

At least 4 children in the United States have died after contracting EV-D68.

[Byline: Olivia Carville]

