[From the CDC report above, there is confirmation that currently 17 cases from 12 states in the USA meet the case definition stated. There is also mention that there have been "dozens" of additional reports received that are currently under investigation. Hence, the 29 cases in the USA that have been reported through news media and posted in previous ProMED-mail reports (see below) represent just a portion of the cases currently under investigation. It is very early in the identification of this recently described polio-like illness and as the CDC update says, one should expect increasing numbers as more suspected cases are evaluated and confirmed.

The status of the investigation into similar cases in Canada is still pending. According the media report there are now 6 cases meeting the case definition at Toronto's Hospital for Sick Children. Previously there had been reports of 2 cases from the same hospital. Presumably the 6 cases of polio-like illness mentioned in the report above include the 2 previously mentioned cases. Laboratory results mentioned above include one EV-D68 infection, and one rhinovirus infection. This increase in 4 cases in Ontario brings the total number of cases in Canada reported in ProMED-mail updates to 17.

We await further information on results of investigations as they become available. More information from knowledgeable sources would be greatly appreciated.

For the HealthMap/ProMED map of the USA, see https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2847183,106.
For the HealthMap/ProMED map of Canada, see https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2847183,274. - Mod.MPP]
